properties.headline: Gale Warning issued February 20 at 8:58AM EST until February 22 at 3:00AM EST by NWS Jacksonville FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, north winds 25 to 35 kt with gusts
around 40 kt and seas 10 to 17 feet with occasional seas to 22
feet expected. For the Small Craft Advisory, North winds around
20 knots with a few gusts to around 35 knots. Seas 4 to 7 feet
with occasional seas to 9 feet expected.

* WHERE...All Northeast Florida coastal waters from Fernandina
Beach FL to Flagler Beach FL out to 60 NM.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 6 PM this evening to 3 AM
EST Saturday. For the Small Craft Advisory, until 6 PM EST
this evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM EST THIS EVENING... ...GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 3 AM EST SATURDAY
